OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBogota begins water        
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Frationing amid severe      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fdrought                    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, About ten million residents of the     
OL,6, Colombian capital Bogota are being     
OL,7, forced to ration water amid crippling  
OL,8, shortages due to a severe drought.     
OL,10,FIt comes as the El Nino climate        
OL,11,Fphenomenon pushes reservoir levels to  
OL,12,Ftheir lowest point in decades.         
OL,14,FOfficials have split the region around 
OL,15,Fthe capital into nine zones - each zone
OL,16,Ftaking turns to switch off water       
OL,17,Fservices for 24 hours.                 
OL,19,FHospitals and schools are exempt. The  
OL,20,Fcity's mayor called the situation dire.
